          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Origin of protons in californium-252 fission"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "J.A.Adams",
                "R.R.Roy"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USAASU"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,NSE,63,41,1977",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,NSE,63,41,1977",
                    "doi": "10.13182/NSE77-A27002",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "NSE",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "63",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "41"
                      },
                      "date": 1977
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#NSR: 1977AD05"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The source consists of a 2-mm-diam spot of 252Cf",
                "deposited on a 2-mm-thick platinum disk. An",
                "aluminum ring mount holds both the source disk and a",
                "9 mg/cm2 thick nickel cover foil. The source has an",
                "activity of 3.e5 fissions per minute."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR",
                "SILI",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A two-detector particle telescope",
                "of the deltaE,E- type is used for energy measurement",
                "and identification of the light charged particles. The",
                "deltaE detector is a 60 mu-m thick, 50 mm2 totally",
                "depleted silicon surface barrier detector, held in a",
                "transmission mount. A 2000 mu-m thick, 80 mm2 lithium",
                "drifted silicon detector is used for the E detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 210Po alpha-particle source was used to calibrate the",
                "telescope system. The calibration was checked by using",
                "the long-range fission alpha particles from 252Cf as a",
                "secondary standard."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For source air and nickel foil energy loss,",
                "    the (n,p) particle telescope background,",
                "    protons simulated by alpha particles detected with",
                "    coincident gamma rays,",
                "    protons from 58Ni(n,p) and 58Ni(alpha,p) reactions",
                "    in the nickel cover foil,",
                "    protons from 14Ni(alpha,p) reaction in air trapped",
                "    beneath the nickel cover foil,",
                "    knock-on protons, from hydrogenous material on the",
                "    surface of the source or on the inner side of the",
                "    cover foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
